Articles.Title: Dua Lipa & Anwar Hadid Split, Long Distance Romance Didn’t Work

Images.Caption: Dua Lipa is back on the market
The couple has been dating each other since June 2019
They were constantly hanging out together
Anwar and Dua have yet to speak publicly about their breakup

Articles.Narration:
Dua Lipa is back on the market after calling it off with her on-again, off-again boyfriend Anwar Hadid.

Sources close to the couple say the 26-year-old pop star and the 22-year-old model have decided to end their 2-year relationship once and for all.

A source spilled the details to Deuxmoi the two have been known to "break up get back together break up get back together." However, an insider says this time it is the real deal and they are done.

The couple has been dating each other since June 2019. Last year, Dua wrote a sweet note on Instagram for their 1-year anniversary. She wrote, "Nothing sweeter than 365 days joint at the hip with you" with a red heart emoji. Anwar replied, "Mi lovely."

Dua was well-liked by Anwar's mother Yolanda Hadid and his sisters Gigi and Bella. They were constantly hanging out together or leaving complimentary comments on each other's social media posts.

Earlier this month, sources spoke to The Sun detailing the struggles the young couple was facing as she recorded an album in London and he lived in New York.
The relationship started after Anwar asked his sister Gigi to hook him up with her friend Dua back in 2019. Dua agreed to the hangout because she was a fan of Anwar too.Anwar and Dua have yet to speak publicly about their breakup.

Articles.Title: Dua Lipa’s “Levitating” Was the Most Popular Song of 2021, Report Finds

Images.Caption: As one of the most popular songs on the album, “Levitating” remained on the Billboard Hot 100 Chart for most of 2021.

Articles.Narration:
Dua Lipa’s “Levitating” Was the Most Popular Song of 2021, Report Finds.

The study attributed an overall increase in music streaming to TikTok.

Dua Lipa’s “Levitating” was the most-streamed song and the most-heard song on the radio in 2021, according to a new report from Billboard and MRC Data.

As one of the most popular songs on the album, “Levitating” remained on the Billboard Hot 100 Chart for most of 2021.

“‘Levitating’ just doing its thing on the Billboard chart is absolutely surreal,” Lipa said during an interview with Billboard’s Pop Shop Podcast. “I mean, that song has really taken a whole life of its own, and it’s been my baby for so long, and to have it out in the world, and for people’s response to be the way that it is, it’s just absolutely mind-blowing to me. So I’m really really really grateful for it all.

Articles.Title: Dua Lipa shows off her winter style after showing off scraped knees
Articles.Narration:
Dua Lipa showed off her winter style in a set of snaps that were shared to her Instagram account on Saturday.

The 26-year-old singer-songwriter cut a seriously stylish figure while wearing several layers of clothing and posing for the impromptu photoshoot.

The performer also shared a shot of her scraped-up knees, and she received the injuries while embarking on her ongoing Future Nostalgia Tour.

She covered up her gorgeous brunette hair with a light blue scarf that was used as a hood.

Dua Lipa previously announced that she would be embarking on a tour in support of Future Nostalgia, which was released in 2020.

The run of shows was initially only set to take place at venues across the United Kingdom and Europe.

However, the singer was forced to postpone all of the dates on her tour due to the onset of the global pandemic two years ago.

Dua Lipa later announced that she was planning to take the show to various locations around the world. 

After months of planning, the Future Nostalgia officially kicked off earlier this month with a show at the FTX Arena in Miami.

Articles.Title: Dua Lipa enjoys slice of pizza with her friend Sarah Lysander

Images.Caption: Dua captioned the slideshow, 'that’s amore' and added pizza and red heart emojis.
The pizza date comes weeks after the singer-songwriter split from boyfriend of two years Anwar Hadid, 22.

Articles.Narration:
Dua Lipa made an appearance on Instagram on Sunday to share new photos with her 77.2 million followers.

In the images the pop star, 26, devoured a mouthwatering slice of pizza with her friend Sarah Lysander, also 26. 

Dua captioned the slideshow, 'that’s amore' and added pizza and red heart emojis. 

The pop star was dressed in her usual fun and quirky style, clad in a knit mint green jacket with a collar.
The first selection in the carousel was a Boomerang that showed the women taking their first bites of the cheesy meal.

The final snap in the post was a closeup view of Dua's elaborate and colorful manicure.

The pizza date comes weeks after the singer-songwriter split from boyfriend of two years Anwar Hadid, 22.

'The couple floated the idea about putting the brakes on their romance last month as traveling so much and being apart is proving too tough,' The Sun reported in December.

Articles.Title: Watch Dua Lipa surprise an 80-year-old superfan on 'The Tonight Show'

Images.Caption: “He’s going to get the surprise of his life" added Lipa.

Articles.Narration:
Dua Lipa surprised an 80-year-old superfan on The Tonight Show after he went viral on TikTok

Late last year, footage of Papa Richy receiving tickets for his 80th birthday to see Dua Lipa on her ‘Future Nostalgia‘ tour was uploaded to TikTok by his grandaughter. The clip, which sees Richy exclaim “Dua Lipa in concert? Are you kidding me?” soon went viral and has racked up almost 2million likes since.

And earlier this week Papa Richy got the chance to meet the pop star during her appearance on The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon.

“We reached out to him, pretending that we were a radio station in New York and told him that he won a contest for the number one TikTok video of the year — he believed this, he loved it,” Fallon explained to the audience. “Yesterday, we flew him and his granddaughter to New York and he thinks he’s about to be interviewed on a radio show and get a tour of 30 Rock. He has no clue what’s going down.”

“He’s going to get the surprise of his life" added Lipa.

Richy was then brought out of a dressing room for his “first radio interview” and led onto The Tonight Show. After a few seconds, he clocked Dua Lipa was standing next to Jimmy Fallon and reacted accordingly. “Oh my god!”

“I read somewhere that one of your dreams is to dance with Dua Lipa,” continued Fallon before The Roots laid down a disco-inspired groove for the pair to dance to.

Articles.Title: Dua Lipa Slammed With Two ‘Levitating’ Copyright Infringement Lawsuits in Four Days

Images.Caption: “Defendants have levitated away plaintiffs’ intellectual property
Florida reggae group called Artikal Sound System

Articles.Narration:
It’s almost become a model in recent years: If a song’s a hit, the copyright-infringement lawsuits follow, and Dua Lipa was clobbered with two of them in four days last week. Her global hit “Levitating,” which has spent 68 weeks on the Billboard Hot 100, has drawn two lawsuits from songwriters claiming the song infringes on their compositions, according to multiple media reports.

The first was filed March 1 by a Florida reggae group called Artikal Sound System, claiming that Lipa’s song lifts from their relatively obscure 2017 track, “Live Your Life.” That complaint includes little specific detail beyond claiming that the two tracks are so similar that it was “highly unlikely that ‘Levitating’ was created independently.”

In the second, more-detailed legal complaint, filed on March 4 in New York, songwriters L. Russell Brown and Sandy Linzer accused Lipa of copying both their 1979 song “Wiggle and Giggle All Night” and 1980 song “Don Diablo,” two tracks dating from the disco era. 

In an unusual statement for a legal complaint, lawyers for Brown and Linzer resorted to puns to make their case: “Defendants have levitated away plaintiffs’ intellectual property,” they wrote. “Plaintiffs bring suit so that defendants cannot wiggle out of their willful infringement.”

Reps for Lipa, Warner Music and the multiple writers and publishers connected to the song either declined or did not immediately respond to Variety’s requests for comment, punning or no.

Articles.Title: Dua Lipa flaunts her peachy posterior in a skimpy  bikini
Articles.Narration:
She is never shy showing off her phenomenal figure on social media.

And Dua Lipa sent temperatures soaring once again on Sunday as she shared a slew of sizzling snaps to her Instagram account.   

The singer, 26, flaunted her very peachy posterior in a tiny multicoloured thong bikini as she took a break from her Future Nostalgia Tour in an unknown idyllic location. 

Cutting a relaxed look, the singer accessorised with some beaded bracelets and hoop earrings while her impressive collection of inking's were clearly on display. 

Dua appeared to be in her element during the getaway as she gave her 80 million viewers a glimpse of how she enjoys her downtime.

She went on to show some photos of the scene which showed a huge canyon and a private pool with some sunbeds. 

Uploading a caption to her breath-taking album she wrote: 'Reset'.

The star left fans guessing of where the exact location was, however, the award winning artist is currently in America on her tour.

On Saturday night she performed in Philadelphia and is set to take to the stage on Monday night in New York.  

The tour - in support of her second studio album Future Nostalgia - has been postponed several times, but finally kicked off in Florida last month. 

Future Nostalgia in March 2021 won the Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album and its lead single Don't Start Now attained critical success, including Grammy noms for Record of the Year, Song of the Year and Best Pop Solo Performance.

Articles.Title: Dua Lipa's strict diet – she never eats after 6pm and fasts every week

Images.Caption: "I try and work out as much as I can."

Articles.Narration:
Dua Lipa has revealed how she stays in such incredible shape.

The New Rules singer opened up about her diet secrets on her brand new podcast Dua Lipa: At Your Service.

Sharing her daily rituals with fans, she said: “I drink a lot of water for my skin. I take vitamins, I take Omega 3.

“I don’t eat after 6pm. I fast. I feel like with my skin it really helps.”

She explained: “When I eat really late my body does not really work through and it takes too long to process food and it does not prepare anything else in my body.”

The 26-year-old shared the key to her diet is all about striking the right balance between healthy and the occasional treat.

For breakfast, her go-tos are eggs or fruit followed by a banana and cashew butter before a workout.

Lunch is chicken salad with vegetables and a cold juice. While dinner is more vegetables with fish.

Speaking to Viva magazine, Dua said: “I try and work out as much as I can.

“I love doing something that’s really fast and quick, like a 15-minute High intensity session which I can do before I start my day.

“If I’ve got a really early call time, I don’t want to be waking up hours before so I do a high intensity workout, shower, breakfast and I’m on my way.”

The moves Dua usually does are moutain climbers, jumping jacks and burpees – although she’s not a massive fan of a plank.

To mix up her workouts, she supplements her training with spinning classes, boxing, yoga and pilates.

Articles.Title: Dua Lipa celebrates her hunky father's 53th birthday

Images.Caption: At the Brit awards in 2019, Dukagin was singled out by the host, Jack Whitehall, as 'the best looking dad in the music industry.'
The 52-year-old was once a popular Kosovar-Albanian rock star

Articles.Narration:
She always causes a stir when she posts photos with her hunky father. 

And Dua Lipa, shared a series of sweet sunkissed snaps with her 'silver fox' dad, Dukagin, to celebrate his 53rd birthday, on Saturday.

Alongside the photos the Don't Start Now singer, 26, penned: 'happy birthday to my papa.'

The pair posed for a series of father daughter holiday snaps in the throwback post, where they donned matching denim tops. 

At the Brit awards in 2019, Dukagin was singled out by the host, Jack Whitehall, as 'the best looking dad in the music industry.' 

'The silver fox over here, the best-looking dad in the music industry. I want to do a dad swap — can you take mine,' the comedian said.    

'Look at Dukagjin! Can we get a camera on this guy?' he continued. 

Dukagjin is no stranger to the stage. The 52-year-old was once a popular Kosovar-Albanian rock star before moving to the UK in 1992.
